Community Pool and Hot Tub', 'This is a cozy one-room cottage with bath (shower) that comfortably sleeps two on a queen-sized bed. A small refrigerator, toaster, coffeemaker (coffee/tea pods, creamer and sugar supplied), dinnerware and microwave allow you to prepare simple meals and picnic lunches for your excursions into the canyon and national forest. The wisteria covered front porch offers a place to kick back/relax with views of the surrounding mountains.We are fully vaccinated and encourage our guests to be the same.The spaceWe are located 4.5 miles from Portal, AZ, in Cave Creek Canyon (we are not in San Simon).  The Southwestern Research Station of the American Museum of Natural History is our neighbor as is the Coronado National Forest which surrounds our property on three sides. Our elevation is 5500’ so we are often 10 or more degrees cooler than the valley below. One national forest trail runs near our property line and is a perfect access to discovering our wildlife: birds, bears, coatimundi, ringtails, etc.Guest accessOur backyard patio is open to our guests (just not the hot tub, please). Enjoy your morning coffee or an evening beer watching the sun rise and/or set. Or enjoy a meal while taking it easy after a long day hiking or birding.Other things to noteWe are newly retired from designing and fabricating exhibits for museums and zoos, so in addition to our very friendly dog, we have various other creatures – all inside our home and none of them dangerous. We are very rural and surrounded by national forest. We keep the cottage very clean (check our reviews) but you might hear the chirp of a cricket in the bathroom or find a moth fluttering near the porch light or lamp by the bed. Nature's local residents are our neighbors.PLEASE NOTE: Our driveway is dirt/gravel and has a relatively steep hill and a few "thank you ma'ams" to direct rainwater off to the side. Higher clearance vehicles are better, but our neighbor's lower Tesla can make it up with no issues. If you have any questions before booking, please click on the ‘Contact Host’ box you will find at the bottom of this listing when you scroll down', 'My house is mostly described by guests as having great energy. Quiet neighborhood on a low traffic street.Guest accessYou will have access to the entire home and garage', "Scottsdale 2BD Comfort Condo with Firepit and Outdoor PoolThe spaceThe Nines delivers world-class amenities, upscale retail, dining, and an exclusive golf course at your doorstep. This lovely 2-bedroom apartment home is in Paradise Valley Village, Scottsdale's most prestigious neighborhood. 

The community provides an abundance of resort-level amenities, including a lagoon-style desert oasis-inspired pool, gas grills, table games, fitness center and a variety of high-class social areas. The apartment sets a new standard for luxury living with contemporary design and spacious interiors. Enjoy a well-equipped kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances, modern décor, and furnishings throughout. You can also relax on your covered patio as you take in the beautiful desert views. Outside your door find endless opportunities to hike, bike, golf and enjoy the area’s attractions. 

Experience the essence of tranquil Scottsdale living and all that the greater Phoenix area has to offer. This exclusive controlled-access community is your perfect home base for year-round special events and activities including Cactus League Spring Training, the Barrett-Jackson Auto Auction and the WM Phoenix Open. 

Enjoy these exciting draws to the Phoenix area. We look forward to hosting you for your next visit to the Valley of the Sun!
